<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <% include ../partials/header.ejs %>
</head>

<body>
<div class="jumbotron text-center">
  <div class="container">
    <a href="/" class="lang-logo">
      <img src="/redbowbox.png">
    </a>
    <h1>Gone Postal</h1>
    <p>This is a simple shipping rate Node.JS application deployed to Heroku.
		<br />It's a reasonably simple app - but a good way to practice new skills.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="container">
  <hr>
  <div id="parcelInformation" class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <h3>Information About Your Parcel</h3>
		<form action="/calculateShipping" method="get">
			<p>Please enter the weight of the item to be shipped.</p>
			<label>Pounds: <input type="number" name="pounds"></label>
			<label>Ounces: <input type="number" name="ounces"></label>
			<p>Please select which type of item will be shipped.</p>
			<select name="type">
				<option selected>Select Mail Type</option>
				<option name="stamped">Stamped Letters</option>
				<option name="metered">Metered Letters</option>
				<option name="flat">Large Flat Envelopes</option>
				<option name="package">First Class Package Service</option>
			</select>
			<br><br>
			<input type="submit" value="Calculate Shipping" class="submitButton">
	  	</form>
    </div>
    <div id="priceEstimate" class="col-md-6">
      <h3>Estimated Shipping Costs</h3>
		<p>Due to the weight of your package: <br>
			Pounds: <%= pounds %> <br>
			Ounces: <%= ounces %> <br> 
			it must ship using <%= type %>.</p>
      	<p>It is estimated it will cost $<%= price %> to ship your package.</p>
    </div>
  </div> <!-- row -->
  <footer class="alert alert-info text-center" role="alert">
	  &copy; 2019 Abrial Marroquin | Template from the <a href="https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-nodejs">Heroku/Express Framework</a> | Created for <a href="https://www.byui.edu">BYU Idaho Online Learning</a>
  </footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
